{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"0900d991a7425ae6f77fe921f154c41d211bc6a111e530da94b6f0e613a833b8","slug":"pages.m15-overview-4-of-4","location":"/pages/200-m15-overview-4-of-4.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Overview (4 of 4)","content_includes_title":false,"authors":[{"nameParsed":{"literal":"Shawn Wiggins","given":"Shawn","family":"Wiggins"},"name":"Shawn Wiggins","affiliations":["City College of San Francisco"],"id":"contributors-myst-generated-uid-0"}],"license":{"content":{"id":"CC-BY-4.0","url":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","name":"Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International","free":true,"CC":true}},"affiliations":[{"id":"City College of San Francisco","name":"City College of San Francisco"}],"numbering":{"title":{"offset":2}},"exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"200-m15-overview-4-of-4.md","url":"/textbook/build/200-m15-overview-4-o-3d2a4b3ed40efa54ce8d9908840bd148.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"admonition","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Learning Objectives","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"Z4ntdvOFxm"}],"key":"jLJpX69Mzm"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"- Explain the logic behind and the process of hypotheses testing. In particular, explain what the p-value is and how it is used to draw conclusions.","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1},"end":{"line":4,"column":1}},"key":"prKn7gD1P3"}],"key":"Yd4K8Nf9P1"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hypothesis testing step 4: Making conclusions.","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"AKnaY2aR6D"}],"key":"PIolWekvVr"}],"key":"jS35rp05z5"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Since our conclusion is based on how small the p-value is, or in other words, how surprising our data are when H~o~ is true, it would be nice to have some kind of guideline or cutoff that will help determine how small the p-value must be, or how “rare” (unlikely) our data must be when H~o~ is true, for us to conclude that we have enough evidence to reject H~o~.","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"key":"SAebLKUfdP"}],"key":"SWqRHs9VJf"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This cutoff exists, and because it is so important, it has a special name. It is called the ","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"doq4drcWbJ"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"significance level of the test","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"aVufzlPZiK"}],"key":"WqDZfA2fVO"},{"type":"text","value":" and is usually denoted by the Greek letter α. The most commonly used significance level is α = .05 (or 5%). This means that:","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"mom6QpzaBF"}],"key":"PW72dK5Vv4"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"if the p-value < α (usually .05), then the data we got is considered to be “rare\n(or surprising) enough” when H ~o~ is true, and we say that the data provide\nsignificant evidence against H ~o~ , so we reject H ~o~ and accept\nH ~a~ .","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"key":"T58U7PhoVX"}],"key":"R3uZooRUcI"}],"key":"zyEcRdqFIc"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"if the p-value > α (usually .05), then our data are not considered to be\n“surprising enough” when H ~o~ is true, and we say that our data do not\nprovide enough evidence to reject H ~o~ (or, equivalently, that the data do\nnot provide enough evidence to accept H ~a~ ).","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"xg0PRNrqIU"}],"key":"g3viHsjzpw"}],"key":"Se6mBDXGj6"}],"key":"aBUTSiF5VD"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":22,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":22,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Important comment about wording.","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":22,"column":1}},"key":"n2r3fuEClT"}],"key":"DJCRxENNeM"}],"key":"XSvTXeAjG6"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Another common wording (mostly in scientific journals) is:","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"key":"Jgl8hq8QRO"}],"key":"RbrU1W2ZUt"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“The results are statistically significant” - when the p-value < α.","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"brcoJnv3Ir"}],"key":"ktE8L2UYBC"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“The results are not statistically significant” - when the p-value > α.","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"key":"Q9AVP0LT53"}],"key":"a2Nlhjmzyr"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Comments","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"bhR01NPS92"}],"identifier":"comments","label":"Comments","html_id":"comments","implicit":true,"key":"bGI3AnF7ga"},{"type":"list","ordered":true,"start":1,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1},"end":{"line":57,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1},"end":{"line":44,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Although the significance level provides a good guideline for drawing\nour conclusions, it should not be treated as an incontrovertible\ntruth.\nThere is a lot of room for personal interpretation. What if your p-value\nis .052? You might want to stick to the rules and say “.052 > .05 and\ntherefore I don’t have enough evidence to reject H~o~”, but you\nmight decide that .052 is small enough for you to believe that\nH~o~ should be rejected. It should be noted that\nscientific journals do consider .05 to be the cutoff point for which any\np-value below the cutoff indicates enough evidence against\nH~o~, and any p-value above it, ","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1},"end":{"line":32,"column":1}},"key":"KVkcZr1dnn"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1},"end":{"line":32,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"or even\nequal to it","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1},"end":{"line":32,"column":1}},"key":"CW30uqdSlo"}],"key":"UEgkX5020L"},{"type":"text","value":", indicates there is not enough evidence against\nH~o~.","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1},"end":{"line":32,"column":1}},"key":"YGhcvBxFGD"}],"key":"Ulo7d6u8Ai"}],"key":"bUQXaFHQAB"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":1},"end":{"line":49,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"It is important to draw your conclusions ","position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":1},"end":{"line":45,"column":1}},"key":"tai0d0SEUk"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":1},"end":{"line":45,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"in context","position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":1},"end":{"line":45,"column":1}},"key":"QDUMD8o86T"}],"key":"oWxD43yBVO"},{"type":"text","value":". It is\n","position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":1},"end":{"line":45,"column":1}},"key":"KAN7UHjwFP"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":1},"end":{"line":45,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"never enough","position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":1},"end":{"line":45,"column":1}},"key":"Dpd52v6jkx"}],"key":"s4FDBDODbf"},{"type":"text","value":" to say: *“p-value = ..., and\ntherefore I have enough evidence to reject H~o~ at the .05\nsignificance level.”*You ","position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":1},"end":{"line":45,"column":1}},"key":"hUtGOG7bEt"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":1},"end":{"line":45,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"should always add:","position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":1},"end":{"line":45,"column":1}},"key":"u4JxfIEt4V"}],"key":"vUYdsQZrTV"},{"type":"text","value":" “... and\nconclude that ... (what it means in the context of the problem)”.","position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":1},"end":{"line":45,"column":1}},"key":"gOx7kml1qN"}],"key":"IANs5EkVDM"}],"key":"n1vXhCX8CU"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":57,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Let’s go back to the issue of the nature of the two types of conclusions\nthat I can make. ","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"key":"phItp8fk48"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Either","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"key":"TJAkc2YmDA"}],"key":"ymPpjRRbAX"},{"type":"text","value":"\n","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"key":"yWeYcB3Wyv"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I reject H~o~ and accept H~a~ (when\nthe p-value is smaller than the significance level)","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"key":"hm4IZO6bNj"}],"key":"wEr9WNqCJE"},{"type":"text","value":"\n","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"key":"yWe6CKVxoi"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"or","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"key":"sZGytQeYR0"}],"key":"JFRR1wvEN5"},{"type":"text","value":"\n","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"key":"wyX3u0pHJc"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I cannot reject H~o~ (when the p-value is\nlarger than the significance level).","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"key":"E5JQlBFQ7Q"}],"key":"go5Vsz4DyJ"}],"key":"e3VVsPpJAZ"}],"key":"qZh38JCDbP"}],"key":"hd61AIIyM7"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":58,"column":1},"end":{"line":58,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As we mentioned earlier, note that the second conclusion does not imply that I accept H~o~, but just that I don’t have enough evidence to reject it. Saying (by mistake) “I don’t have enough evidence to reject H~o~ so I accept it” indicates that the data provide evidence that H~o~ is true, which is ","position":{"start":{"line":58,"column":1},"end":{"line":58,"column":1}},"key":"yff5VakctG"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":58,"column":1},"end":{"line":58,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"not necessarily the case","position":{"start":{"line":58,"column":1},"end":{"line":58,"column":1}},"key":"OwGKDq4BST"}],"key":"sbuLcauWzs"},{"type":"text","value":". Consider the following slightly artificial yet effective example:","position":{"start":{"line":58,"column":1},"end":{"line":58,"column":1}},"key":"ID24tDEh1A"}],"key":"awg9Xa5cW2"},{"type":"admonition","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Example","position":{"start":{"line":60,"column":1},"end":{"line":60,"column":1}},"key":"v1auHPaDpB"}],"key":"M4mpoaWzGY"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"An employer claims to subscribe to an \"equal opportunity\" policy, not hiring men any more often than women for managerial positions. Is this credible? You're not sure, so you want to test the following *two hypotheses:*\n\n- *H~o~:* The proportion of male managers hired is\n                                .5\n- *H~a~:* The proportion of male managers hired is\n                                more than .5\n\n*Data:* You choose at random three of the new managers who were hired in the last 5 years and find that all 3 are men.\n\n*Assessing Evidence:* If the proportion of male managers hired is really .5 (H~o~ is true), then the probability that the random selection of three managers will yield three males is therefore .5 * .5 * .5 = .125. This is the p-value.\n\n*Conclusion:* Using .05 as the significance level, you conclude that since the p-value = .125 > .05, the fact that the three randomly selected mangers were all males is not enough evidence to reject H~o~. In other words, you do not have enough evidence to reject the employer's claim of subscribing to an equal opportunity policy.\n\nHowever, *the data (all three selected are males) definitely does not provide evidence to accept the employer's claim (H~o~).*","position":{"start":{"line":61,"column":1},"end":{"line":74,"column":1}},"key":"MGc2wluiaS"}],"key":"u2MsHBz5J9"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":77,"column":1},"end":{"line":77,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Learn By Doing","position":{"start":{"line":77,"column":1},"end":{"line":77,"column":1}},"key":"jFt3WCaRXV"}],"identifier":"learn-by-doing","label":"Learn By Doing","html_id":"learn-by-doing","implicit":true,"key":"WwohcnwB16"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":79,"column":1},"end":{"line":79,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The following two hypotheses are tested:","position":{"start":{"line":79,"column":1},"end":{"line":79,"column":1}},"key":"Ckzp47PwxS"}],"key":"BAQUGUsqtq"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":85,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":82,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"H~o~: The proportion of U.S. adults who oppose gay marriage is\nroughly 50%.","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"key":"URiPcHnMVL"}],"key":"Rrs3Hi89yY"}],"key":"CZeDTbSgrW"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":85,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"H~a~: The proportion of U.S. adults who oppose gay marriage is\nabove 50% (i.e., the majority oppose).","position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":83,"column":1}},"key":"CRT27UZtmW"}],"key":"L069e0Uqsq"}],"key":"MoxDx5ZlMd"}],"key":"WLvnsztPpo"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":86,"column":1},"end":{"line":86,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Suppose a survey was conducted in which a random sample of 1,100 U.S. adults was asked about their opinions about gay marriage, and based on the data, the p-value was found to be .002.","position":{"start":{"line":86,"column":1},"end":{"line":86,"column":1}},"key":"af0Khulm2C"}],"key":"DXHIa6r7pN"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":88,"column":1},"end":{"line":88,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Comment: Throughout this activity use a .05 (5%) significance level (cutoff).","position":{"start":{"line":88,"column":1},"end":{"line":88,"column":1}},"key":"wzyHECGk5C"}],"key":"esnspuiuHh"},{"type":"admonition","kind":"note","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Note","key":"xtWTVEck9P"}],"key":"cVXpmWKvtr"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"**Sectionnest**\n\n*(Interactive activity — available in the OLI platform)*","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":93,"column":1}},"key":"rS8SbJ3GAh"}],"key":"nbXvjPDjPG"},{"type":"admonition","kind":"note","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Note","key":"mp05SPJDHJ"}],"key":"Fw721hIsFZ"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"**Sectionnest**\n\n*(Interactive activity — available in the OLI platform)*","position":{"start":{"line":97,"column":1},"end":{"line":99,"column":1}},"key":"t120VCtiZN"}],"key":"sEBNE1HBwj"},{"type":"admonition","kind":"note","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Note","key":"wgRn900aJo"}],"key":"sVrEXrtqVP"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"**Sectionnest**\n\n*(Interactive activity — available in the OLI platform)*","position":{"start":{"line":103,"column":1},"end":{"line":105,"column":1}},"key":"aZDZFqUYp7"}],"key":"OuKRUUkgGU"},{"type":"admonition","kind":"note","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Note","key":"bksZglYn79"}],"key":"OT6NnS3UmN"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"**Sectionnest**\n\n*(Interactive activity — available in the OLI platform)*","position":{"start":{"line":109,"column":1},"end":{"line":111,"column":1}},"key":"FlQn2Ag6xt"}],"key":"BNcgT3E7AW"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"posi